<paragraph blockId="3.[452,864,746,806]" box="[555,760,781,806]" pageId="3">
(
<figureCitation box="[563,665,781,806]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="3.[160,225,635,658]" captionTargetBox="[162,1152,142,603]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[162,1153,142,604]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 1. Pealius satakshiae Dubey sp. nov., habitus: (a) puparium on Quercus leucotrichophora; (b) vasiform orifice in pyriform pit." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3654791" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3654791/files/figure.png" pageId="3">Figures 1</figureCitation>
(a) 
<emphasis box="[700,714,781,806]" italics="true" pageId="3">–</emphasis>
5(f))
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[160,1156,868,1101]" box="[160,294,868,894]" pageId="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,294,868,894]" italics="true" pageId="3">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[160,1156,868,1101]" pageId="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,283,902,928]" italics="true" pageId="3">Puparium.</emphasis>
Broadly oval; median and submedian area dark brown, submargin slightly raised, light brown (
<figureCitation box="[387,474,939,963]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="3.[160,225,635,658]" captionTargetBox="[162,1152,142,603]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[162,1153,142,604]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 1. Pealius satakshiae Dubey sp. nov., habitus: (a) puparium on Quercus leucotrichophora; (b) vasiform orifice in pyriform pit." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3654791" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3654791/files/figure.png" pageId="3">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(a)); without secretion of wax over dorsum and periphery of margin, but small amount of white wax may be present in caudal and thoracic tracheal pore openings; vasiform orifice in a pit (
<figureCitation box="[598,683,1008,1032]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="3.[160,225,635,658]" captionTargetBox="[162,1152,142,603]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[162,1153,142,604]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 1. Pealius satakshiae Dubey sp. nov., habitus: (a) puparium on Quercus leucotrichophora; (b) vasiform orifice in pyriform pit." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3654791" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3654791/files/figure.png" pageId="3">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(b)), but not so prominent in slide mounts; found singly on lower surface of leaves, one puparium per leaf; dimorphic, female 
<quantity box="[160,327,1077,1101]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" metricValueMax="1.225" metricValueMin="1.175" pageId="3" unit="mm" value="1200.0" valueMax="1225.0" valueMin="1175.0">
<date box="[160,283,1077,1101]" pageId="3" value="1175" valueMax="1225">
1175 
<emphasis box="[215,228,1077,1101]" italics="true" pageId="3">–</emphasis>
1225
</date>
µm
</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[398,566,1077,1101]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.081" metricValueMax="1.1" metricValueMin="1.062" pageId="3" unit="mm" value="1081.0" valueMax="1100.0" valueMin="1062.0">
<date box="[398,521,1077,1101]" pageId="3" value="1062" valueMax="1100">
1062 
<emphasis box="[453,466,1077,1101]" italics="true" pageId="3">–</emphasis>
1100
</date>
µm
</quantity>
wide; male 
<quantity box="[703,788,1077,1101]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.75" pageId="3" unit="mm" value="975.0">975 µm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[859,945,1077,1101]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.25" pageId="3" unit="mm" value="825.0">825 µm</quantity>
wide.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[160,1155,1146,1276]" pageId="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,252,1146,1172]" italics="true" pageId="3">Margin.</emphasis>
Regularly crenulate (
<figureCitation box="[509,608,1148,1172]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="4.[159,224,868,891]" captionTargetBox="[165,1148,148,833]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[161,1151,142,837]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 2. Pealius satakshiae Dubey sp. nov., camera lucida drawings: (a) puparium, dorsal view; (b) marginal crenulations; (c) vasiform orifice." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3654795" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3654795/files/figure.png" pageId="3">Figure 2</figureCitation>
(b)), 7 
<emphasis box="[677,690,1148,1172]" italics="true" pageId="3">–</emphasis>
10 crenulations in 
<quantity box="[914,1007,1148,1172]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="3" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.1 mm</quantity>
. Caudal and thoracic tracheal combs indicated in the margin (
<figureCitation box="[728,822,1182,1206]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="5.[160,225,1491,1514]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,143,1459]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[163,1153,142,1459]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 3. Pealius satakshiae Dubey sp. nov., holotype: (a) puparium; (b) submargin; (c) thoracic tracheal comb; (d) caudal tracheal comb; (e) cephalothorax, cephalus differentiation; (f) abdominal segment sutures, reduced segment VII; (g) prothoracic tubercle; (h) operculum, lingula." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3654799" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3654799/files/figure.png" pageId="3">Figure 3</figureCitation>
(c,d)) with a tuberclulate fold of dorsal cuticle. Thoracic tracheal furrows absent. Caudal tracheal furrow marked with transverse plates for some distance, posterior to vasiform orifice.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[160,1156,1320,1727]" lastBlockId="4.[160,1156,979,1211]" lastPageId="4" pageId="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,500,1320,1346]" pageId="3">
Dorsum 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,500,1320,1346]" italics="true" pageId="3">
(
<figureCitation box="[272,379,1320,1346]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[160,225,1493,1516]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1462]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[163,1153,142,1462]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 4. Pealius satakshiae Dubey sp. nov., scanning electron microscope (SEM) photomicrographs: (a) puparium, dorsal sculptures; (b) florate form of thoracic opening; (c) vasiform orifice in pit; (d) cephalic seta; (e) cephalothoracic suture and tubercle; (f) abdominal segmentation; (g) margin; (h) operculum, lingula, eighth abdominal setae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3654803" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3654803/files/figure.png" pageId="3">Figures 4</figureCitation>
(a–h)ı 5d).
</emphasis>
</emphasis>
Submargin broad, faintly demarcated from the dorsal disc by a faint ridge (
<figureCitation box="[341,431,1357,1381]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[160,225,1493,1516]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1462]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[163,1153,142,1462]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 4. Pealius satakshiae Dubey sp. nov., scanning electron microscope (SEM) photomicrographs: (a) puparium, dorsal sculptures; (b) florate form of thoracic opening; (c) vasiform orifice in pit; (d) cephalic seta; (e) cephalothoracic suture and tubercle; (f) abdominal segmentation; (g) margin; (h) operculum, lingula, eighth abdominal setae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3654803" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3654803/files/figure.png" pageId="3">Figure 4</figureCitation>
(a)). Longitudinal moulting suture reaching margin and transverse moulting suture extending to and merging with submarginal lines. A pair of tubercles present on submedian area of pro- and metathorax (
<figureCitation box="[777,872,1426,1450]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[160,225,1493,1516]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1462]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[163,1153,142,1462]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 4. Pealius satakshiae Dubey sp. nov., scanning electron microscope (SEM) photomicrographs: (a) puparium, dorsal sculptures; (b) florate form of thoracic opening; (c) vasiform orifice in pit; (d) cephalic seta; (e) cephalothoracic suture and tubercle; (f) abdominal segmentation; (g) margin; (h) operculum, lingula, eighth abdominal setae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3654803" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3654803/files/figure.png" pageId="3">Figure 4</figureCitation>
(e)). Cephalothoracic and abdominal segment sutures prominent, not reaching subdorsal area, abdominal segments rhachisform on submedian area (
<figureCitation box="[531,624,1495,1519]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[160,225,1493,1516]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1462]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[163,1153,142,1462]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 4. Pealius satakshiae Dubey sp. nov., scanning electron microscope (SEM) photomicrographs: (a) puparium, dorsal sculptures; (b) florate form of thoracic opening; (c) vasiform orifice in pit; (d) cephalic seta; (e) cephalothoracic suture and tubercle; (f) abdominal segmentation; (g) margin; (h) operculum, lingula, eighth abdominal setae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3654803" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3654803/files/figure.png" pageId="3">Figure 4</figureCitation>
(f)). Intersegmental sutures prominently spaced. Submarginal lines prominent (
<figureCitation box="[491,581,1530,1554]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[160,225,1493,1516]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1462]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[163,1153,142,1462]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 4. Pealius satakshiae Dubey sp. nov., scanning electron microscope (SEM) photomicrographs: (a) puparium, dorsal sculptures; (b) florate form of thoracic opening; (c) vasiform orifice in pit; (d) cephalic seta; (e) cephalothoracic suture and tubercle; (f) abdominal segmentation; (g) margin; (h) operculum, lingula, eighth abdominal setae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3654803" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3654803/files/figure.png" pageId="3">Figure 4</figureCitation>
(g)). Submedian depressions present on anterior part of each cephalothoracic and abdominal segment. Median length of cephalothorax and abdomen as measured equal, or the abdomen (
<quantity box="[675,812,1599,1623]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.495" metricValueMax="6.1" metricValueMin="4.89" pageId="3" unit="mm" value="549.5" valueMax="610.0" valueMin="489.0">
489 
<emphasis box="[716,729,1599,1623]" italics="true" pageId="3">–</emphasis>
610 µm
</quantity>
long) is slightly longer than the cephalothorax (
<quantity box="[331,472,1634,1658]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.35" metricValueMax="5.91" metricValueMin="4.79" pageId="3" unit="mm" value="535.0" valueMax="591.0" valueMin="479.0">
479 
<emphasis box="[373,386,1634,1658]" italics="true" pageId="3">–</emphasis>
591 µm
</quantity>
long). Abdominal segment VII much reduced medially as the pockets of segment VIII reaching anteriorly and overlapping intersegmental suture of VI/ VII. Median length of pro-, meso- and metathorax: 102 
<emphasis box="[820,833,1703,1727]" italics="true" pageId="3">–</emphasis>
112, 67 
<emphasis box="[920,933,1703,1727]" italics="true" pageId="3">–</emphasis>
80 and 
<quantity box="[1032,1152,1703,1727]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.35" metricValueMax="7.5" metricValueMin="7.2" pageId="3" unit="mm" value="73.5" valueMax="75.0" valueMin="72.0">
72 
<emphasis box="[1058,1071,1703,1727]" italics="true" pageId="3">–</emphasis>
75 µm
</quantity>
, respectively, in female; 92, 62 and 
<quantity box="[531,603,979,1003]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="4" unit="mm" value="60.0">60 µm</quantity>
, respectively, in male. Median length of abdominal segments I 
<emphasis box="[280,293,1014,1038]" italics="true" pageId="4">–</emphasis>
VIII (A1 
<emphasis box="[370,383,1014,1038]" italics="true" pageId="4">–</emphasis>
A8): A1: 50 
<emphasis box="[502,515,1014,1038]" italics="true" pageId="4">–</emphasis>
63, A2: 35 
<emphasis box="[623,636,1014,1038]" italics="true" pageId="4">–</emphasis>
45, A3: 25 
<emphasis box="[745,758,1014,1038]" italics="true" pageId="4">–</emphasis>
55, A4: 37 
<emphasis box="[867,880,1014,1038]" italics="true" pageId="4">–</emphasis>
53, A5: 42 
<emphasis box="[988,1001,1014,1038]" italics="true" pageId="4">–</emphasis>
47, A6: 63 
<emphasis box="[1110,1123,1014,1038]" italics="true" pageId="4">–</emphasis>
68, A7: 0, A8: 
<quantity box="[266,376,1049,1073]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.55" metricValueMax="6.8" metricValueMin="6.3" pageId="4" unit="mm" value="65.5" valueMax="68.0" valueMin="63.0">
63 
<emphasis box="[293,306,1049,1073]" italics="true" pageId="4">–</emphasis>
68 µm
</quantity>
in the female, and A1: 48, A2: 35, A3: 43, A4: 40, A5: 38, A6: 48, A7: 0, A8: 
<quantity box="[160,233,1083,1107]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="4" unit="mm" value="55.0">55 µm</quantity>
in the male. Abdominal segment VIII forms a triangular figure. Distance between posterior end of vasiform orifice and caudal opening measured 
<quantity box="[882,1021,1118,1142]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.535" metricValueMax="1.5699999999999998" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="4" unit="mm" value="153.5" valueMax="157.0" valueMin="150.0">
150 
<emphasis box="[922,935,1118,1142]" italics="true" pageId="4">–</emphasis>
157 µm
</quantity>
long in the female (
<quantity box="[251,340,1153,1177]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="4" unit="mm" value="110.0">110 µm</quantity>
long in the male), furrow 
<quantity box="[648,762,1153,1177]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.4" metricValueMax="4.8" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="4" unit="mm" value="44.0" valueMax="48.0" valueMin="40.0">
40 
<emphasis box="[674,687,1153,1177]" italics="true" pageId="4">–</emphasis>
48 µm
</quantity>
wide posterior to vasiform orifice. Geminate pores large, each occupying an area 
<quantity box="[680,738,1187,1211]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="4" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 µm</quantity>
in length.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3654795" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3654795" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3654795/files/figure.png" pageId="4" startId="4.[159,224,868,891]" targetBox="[165,1148,148,833]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[159,1154,868,921]" pageId="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[159,250,868,891]" pageId="4">Figure 2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Dubey" authorityName="Dubey &amp; Singh" authorityYear="2019" box="[259,507,868,892]" class="Insecta" family="Aleyrodidae" genus="Pealius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="satakshiae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[259,434,868,891]" italics="true" pageId="4">Pealius satakshiae</emphasis>
Dubey
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[515,596,869,892]" pageId="4" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, camera lucida drawings: (a) puparium, dorsal view; (b) marginal crenulations; (c) vasiform orifice.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[160,1156,1270,1435]" pageId="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,359,1270,1296]" italics="true" pageId="4">Vasiform orifice.</emphasis>
Located in an elongate oval pit, posteriorly; elongate subcordate, posteriorly provided with transverse plates for some distance (
<figureCitation box="[890,988,1307,1331]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[160,225,1493,1516]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1462]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[163,1153,142,1462]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 4. Pealius satakshiae Dubey sp. nov., scanning electron microscope (SEM) photomicrographs: (a) puparium, dorsal sculptures; (b) florate form of thoracic opening; (c) vasiform orifice in pit; (d) cephalic seta; (e) cephalothoracic suture and tubercle; (f) abdominal segmentation; (g) margin; (h) operculum, lingula, eighth abdominal setae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3654803" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3654803/files/figure.png" pageId="4">Figure 4</figureCitation>
(h)), 
<quantity box="[1039,1155,1306,1331]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.75" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.5" pageId="4" unit="mm" value="57.5" valueMax="60.0" valueMin="55.0">
55 
<emphasis box="[1067,1080,1306,1330]" italics="true" pageId="4">–</emphasis>
60 µm
</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[225,338,1341,1365]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.6" metricValueMax="5.7" metricValueMin="5.5" pageId="4" unit="mm" value="56.0" valueMax="57.0" valueMin="55.0">
55 
<emphasis box="[252,265,1341,1365]" italics="true" pageId="4">–</emphasis>
57 µm
</quantity>
wide (55 × 
<quantity box="[476,549,1341,1365]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="4" unit="mm" value="50.0">50 µm</quantity>
in the male); operculum subcordate, 
<quantity box="[977,1091,1341,1365]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.15" metricValueMax="3.3" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="4" unit="mm" value="31.5" valueMax="33.0" valueMin="30.0">
30 
<emphasis box="[1005,1018,1341,1365]" italics="true" pageId="4">–</emphasis>
33 µm
</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[160,272,1376,1400]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="3.7" pageId="4" unit="mm" value="41.0" valueMax="45.0" valueMin="37.0">
37 
<emphasis box="[187,200,1376,1400]" italics="true" pageId="4">–</emphasis>
45 µm
</quantity>
wide (27 × 
<quantity box="[406,477,1376,1400]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7" pageId="4" unit="mm" value="37.0">37 µm</quantity>
in the male); lingula exposed, D-shaped, slightly constricted at base, not extending beyond posterior margin of the orifice.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[160,1156,1493,1727]" pageId="4">
